cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.GT, cs.CC, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with computational complexity of flooding games on graphs with interval representations, which involves concepts from graph theory, computational geometry, and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also involves analysis of the computational complexity of the game, which could fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
